parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the infotainment system can cause a loss of critical information, such as speed and navigation, which can lead to accidents or confusion while driving.
symptoms: The infotainment system goes dark or reboots while driving
causing a loss of display and functionality.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Electrical system malfunctions can cause a loss of power, reduced performance, and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: Error messages appear on the dashboard
such as "12V power supply" or "electrical system malfunction
" and the vehicle may shut down or reduce performance.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Door malfunctions can cause safety risks, such as doors opening while driving or failing to lock properly.
symptoms: Doors may open or unlock while driving
or may not lock properly when parked.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Clutch and transmission issues can cause difficulty shifting gears, leading to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
or the vehicle shifts into "park" unexpectedly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Horn failure can increase the risk of accidents, as the driver may not be able to alert other drivers or pedestrians.
symptoms: The horn fails to work
even when the vehicle is in good condition.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Power window issues can cause safety risks, such as windows opening unexpectedly or failing to close properly.
symptoms: The front passenger window may open or close unexpectedly
or may not respond to controls.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Charging port issues can cause safety risks, such as water ingress or electrical shock.
symptoms: The charging port door may fall off
or water may enter the charging port.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Vehicle performance and range issues can cause safety risks, such as reduced speed or unexpected loss of power.
symptoms: The vehicle may not achieve its advertised range
or may experience reduced performance or unexpected loss of power.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the infotainment system can cause distraction, loss of important information, and potentially lead to accidents.
symptoms: The center infotainment screen goes black
the driver information screen (instrument cluster) turns off
and the system reboots while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the doors can cause safety hazards, such as unintended opening or closing while driving, and potentially lead to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The driver-side door opens and closes by itself
locks and unlocks itself
and may not open or close properly. The door may also unlatch randomly while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended acceleration can cause loss of control, accidents, and potentially lead to injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates unexpectedly
sometimes without the driver's input
and may continue to accelerate even when the driver attempts to brake.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the backup camera can cause reduced visibility, increasing the risk of accidents or injuries while reversing.
symptoms: The backup camera flickers intermittently
and the system continues to malfunction even after repairs.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the windows can cause distraction, discomfort, and potentially lead to accidents.
symptoms: The window control malfunctions
causing the window to go down instead of up
and may require the window to be fully lowered before it can be raised again.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the vehicle computer system can cause loss of important information, distraction, and potentially lead to accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle computer system shuts down and restarts
causing instruments to go grey
and may affect the overall safety and performance of the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the door latch can cause the door to open or unlock while the vehicle is in motion, which can lead to accidents or injuries to occupants.
symptoms: The door unlatches or opens while driving
the door does not close properly
the door handle fails to operate
the central locking function malfunctions
the door locks or unlocks randomly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The optical windshield distortion can affect peripheral vision, increasing the risk of accidents, especially when driving at night or in low-light conditions.
symptoms: Visible distortion on the windshield
affecting peripheral vision
noticeable in full light conditions
not visible in shade.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the door locking system can cause the doors to lock or unlock randomly, trapping occupants inside or outside the vehicle, which can lead to safety risks, especially in emergency situations.
symptoms: Doors lock or unlock randomly
doors do not open or close properly
central locking function malfunctions
remote key does not work.
